race.description: Festive Season Racing Sunday Dec 21 Handicap (C3)
race.comment: SHAZAIR (4) is a promising galloper who was beaten 1L at Belmont first up before winning a CL1 there over 1400m. It was a tough effort from the 13 barrier and the step up to the mile will hold no fears. Keeps a leading hoop and fitter she can go on with the job. FOREVER DREAMING (5) was quickly back on track when beaten 1L this grade at Belmont. She hasn't won at 1600m but gets her chance in this line-up. BATTLE COMMANDER (1) won at Ascot and then missed a nose at Belmont, before improving his figures again beaten 2.7L at Ascot over 1800m. Positions forward and gets in well with the 3kg allowance. He has claims as well. BONDI BAY (3) will be fitter and is much better than the form line suggests. Up to the mile helps and he's placed 2/2 third-up. Has the inside barrier, and Brad Parnham goes on.
